Mr Paul Okpe has assumed office as the new Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in Edo State. This was contained in a statement issued in Benin on Monday by Uchenna Nnadika, spokesman of the sector. Okpe, until his recent appointment, was the Sector Commander in Osun State. Nnadika further disclosed that Okpe hailed from the FCT and held a BA in English from the Ahmadu Bello University Zaria (ABU). (NAN) 